From Chris Hand Subject Re Lead Acid batteries Concrete Carter Ames wrote Why does a lead acid battery discharge and become dead totally unuseable when stored on a concrete floor It could be that you stored it somewhere that it could become covered by moisture or damp air which would short out the The same thing happens to my car Citroen damp gets under the bonnet US hood and shorts the spark plugs to earth so it won't The solution for the car is to clean the plug leads and spray with WD moisture repellant If damp is the problem then storing the battery off the ground may I'm not sure if spraying with WD would be safe since it is very flammable high percentage petroleum Just a Chris Chris Hand Lecturer Internet mail Dept of Computing Science Voice De Montfort University The Gateway Fax FIDOnet LEICESTER UK Linux free unix for IBM PCs